Eragrostis chloromelas

    Authority   Ste.
      Family    Liliopsida:Commelinidae:Cyperales:Gramineae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 5727

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A strongly tufted grass with dense clumps reaching a
   height of 40-90 cm. USES It is used for fodder and erosion control.
   GROWING PERIOD Perennial growing spring to autumn. COMMON NAMES Boer
   lovegrass. FURTHER INF Boer lovegrass is native of Africa and
   introduced to the United States.

   Sources
   SOURCES (E. chloromelas Steud.)
   Skerman P 1990 pp 413-414 [KTMP, RAIN, DRA, TEXT, PH]
   Duke J 1979 pp 95 [PH, RAIN, TEMP]
   Duke J 1975 pp 16 [PH, RAIN, TEMP]
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 71 [USE]

